<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>hide and hair • neither hide nor hair</xh5><p> <i>hide and hair</i>—(coll.) 1. completely; wholly: And I don’t mean to do the thing by halves. No; I shall save you, <u>hide and hair</u>. 2. <i>(in the phrase “eat someone up hide and hair”)</i> hurt or otherwise seriously harm a person: Mother had often said that anybody could eat us up <u>hide and hair</u> before help arrived from the camp.</p><p> <i>neither hide nor hair</i>—(coll.) not a trace of a person’s presence; nothing whatever: The bank was robbed two months ago, but the police could find <u>neither hide nor hair</u> of the criminals yet.</p> </entry>
